#Text=John Halle
#Text=For other people named Main Page , see Main Page ( disambiguation ) .
#Text=1565 woodcut
#Text=John Halle
#Text=, or John Hall of Maidstone ( c. 1529/1530 – c. 1568 ) [ 1 ] was an English surgeon , known as a medical writer and poet .
#Text=Life
#Text=Born in 1529 or 1530 , Halle became a member of the Worshipful Company of Chirurgeons , and practised as a surgeon at Maidstone , Kent . [ 2 ]
#Text=He is thought to have been a supporter of Thomas Wyatt the younger , and involved in Wyatt 's rebellion . [ 1 ]
#Text=Works
#Text=As a poet , Halle was influenced by Thomas Wyatt the elder . [ 1 ]
#Text=His works were : [ 2 ]
#Text=Certayne Chapters taken out of the Proverbes of Solomon , with other Chapters of the Holy Scripture , and certayne Psalmes of David , translated into English Metre
#Text=, London ( Thomas Raynalde ) , 1549 .

#Text=A Poesie in Forme of a Vision , briefly inveying against the most hatefull and prodigious artes of Necromancie , Witchcraft , Sorcerie , Incantations , and divers other detestable and deuilishe practises , dayly used under colour of Judiciall Astrologie
#Text=, London , 1563 .
#Text=The Court of Vertue , contayning many Holy or Spretuall Songes , Sonnettes , Psalmes , Balletts , and Shorte Sentences , as well of Holy Scripture , as others
#Text=, with musical notes , London , 1565 .
#Text=This book seems by the prologue to have been written to contrast with The Court of Venus , a collection of love songs . [ 2 ]
#Text=Dedicated to Thomas Cole . [ 1 ]

#Text=A most excellent and learned woorke of chirurgerie , called Chirurgia parva Lanfranci , Lanfranke of Mylayne his briefe : reduced from dyvers translations to our vulgar-frase , and now first published in the Englyshe prynte
#Text=, black letter , 4 pts . , London , 1565 .
#Text=Translation from Lanfranc of Milan .
#Text=It contains a woodcut portrait of the translator , " æt . 35 , 1564 " .

#Text=Appended were two other works : A very frutefull and necessary briefe worke of Anatomie ; and An Historiall Expostulation : Against the beastlye Abusers , both of Chyrurgerie , and Physyke , in oure tyme : with a goodlye Doctrine and Instruction , necessarye to be marked and folowed , of all true Chirurgiens , reprinted in volume 11 of the publications of the Percy Society , London , 1844 , edited by Thomas Joseph Pettigrew .
#Text=Halle denounced in the latter the quacks of the day , and opposed the combination of magic , divination , and physic .

#Text=A metrical version of The Prouerbes of Salamon , thre chapters of Ecclesiastes , the sixthe chapter of Sapientia , the ix chapter of Ecclesiasticus , and certayne psalmes of Dauid , London ( Edward Whitchurch ) , n. d. , dedicated to John Bricket , esq . , of Eltham .
#Text=Halle complained that chapters of the Book of Proverbs , translated by him into English metre , 1550 , had been attributed to Thomas Sternhold .

#Text=English translation of Benedict Victorius Faventinus 's and Niccolò Massa ' s treatises De Morbo Gallico ; Cure of the French Disease , a manuscript in the Bodleian Library , which also contains letters from Halle to William Cuningham .
#Text=Commendatory verses
#Text=, in English , prefixed to Thomas Gale ' s Enchiridion of Chirurgerie , 1563 , and to the same author 's Institution of a Chirurgian , 1563 .
